{Speech 10}{}{Let me give you a shot... Done.}
{Speech 11}{}{I can rid you of this problem, but it'll cost you 900 coins. Sorry, I can't do it for free - we have to buy these medicines ourselves.}
{Speech 11 Answer Exit}{}{That's a bit pricey, I can't afford it right now.}
{Speech 11 Answer 12}{}{Forget the money, Doc, I'm tired of suffering. I'm ready to pay.}
{Speech 11 Answer 13}{}{Hey, old man, you'll give me this for free, or I'll break your arm.}
{Speech 12}{}{Excellent. Eat this powder... And this pill... And wash it down with water.}
{Speech 12 Answer Exit}{}{[Take the medicine]}
{Speech 12 Answer Exit*}{}{Nah, I changed my mind.}
{Speech 13}{}{HELP!!!}
{Speech 14}{}{Pleased to meet you, @pname@. My name is Doctor Mark Brompton. You can just call me Doc.}
{Speech 14 Answer 16}{}{And what do you do here?}
{Speech 14 Answer 3}{}{A doctor, huh? I need medical help.}
{Speech 14 Answer 35}{}{A doctor, huh? I need medical help.}
{Speech 14 Answer 9}{}{I want to buy some medicine.}
{Speech 14 Answer 15}{}{I see. Well, I was just looking around. If anything comes up, I'll know where to go! Goodbye, doctor!}
{Speech 15}{}{Goodbye.}
{Speech 16}{}{Healing the sick, what else would a doctor do. Speak up quick, what brings you here, I've still got two amputations today.@@Healing the sick, what else would a doctor do. Plenty of patients, mostly gecko bites.@@Healing the sick, what else would a doctor do. Plenty of patients - the natives are learning to handle firearms, the Vault folk are learning to hunt. The first lot keep shooting their feet, the second lot are nothing but bites.@@Healing the sick, what else would a doctor do. Plenty of patients. One lost a nail, another a leg. Everyone's got their own.}
{Speech 16 Answer 17}{}{Can you reattach a leg?}
{Speech 16 Answer 3}{}{Doctor, I need help.}
{Speech 16 Answer 9}{}{I want to buy some medicine. Can I do that here?}
{Speech 16 Answer 15}{}{I see. Well, thanks for the info!}
{Speech 17}{}{Bring it over - we'll see. Not every leg can be reattached anywhere... To the head, for instance, it's especially hard to attach. And I've never once managed to attach a gecko's paw - rejection.}
{Speech 17 Answer Exit}{}{You know, I feel a bit uneasy here, I'll go get some air...}
{Speech 17 Answer 3}{}{Doctor, I've got, uh, a problem!}
{Speech 17 Answer 9}{}{How about I just buy a "put yourself back together" kit from you instead...}
{Speech 17 Answer Exit*}{}{I'll keep that in mind, see you soon!}
{Speech 18}{}{[The doctor squints one eye and looks at you closely] Here, take this, it helps with memory problems. [Hands over a pack of Mentats]}
{Speech 18 Answer Exit}{}{Oh! Thanks, doctor!}
{Speech 18 Answer 3}{}{Thanks, doctor! But that's not what I'm here for. I need medical help.}
{Speech 18 Answer 9}{}{Thanks! I'd like to buy some more medicine.}
